          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Ecowas exit</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-30-1.png" alt="Ecowas exit" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Niger, Mali, and Burkina Faso officially withdrew from the ECOWAS block and formed their alliance of Sahel states.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Niger, Mali, and Burkina Faso have <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-h1-1-officially-withdrawn" target="_blank">officially withdrawn</a> from the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS). ECOWAS has requested that the other members of the bloc continue to offer citizens of these three countries the same privileges as if they were still members, such as the free movement of people and goods. The bloc wants to keep the door open so the three members can return.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">These three states make up the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-h1-2-alliance-of-the-sahel-states" target="_blank">Alliance of Sahel states</a>. This is a significant blow to the ECOWAS bloc, which has struggled with competing interests with Russia and the West, Islamist armed groups, and a series of coups. The split worsens the legitimacy crisis of ECOWAS, which has often failed people’s expectations in upholding the rule of law.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Many citizens of these three countries welcome the move. They find it a relief and cut the cords of French imperialism. They feel ECOWAS is too closely linked with France, and this move is a way to assert its independence. Analysts say it’s an unprecedented blow to the group that could threaten efforts to return democracy and help stabilize the increasingly fragile region.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
