          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">M23 captures Goma</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Fight continues in the DRC with the M23 rebel group takeover of the city of Goma, leading to more deaths, displacements, and embassy raids.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          Fighting in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has escalated deeply. Rwandan-backed M23 rebel group <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-h3-7-has-taken-over" target="_blank">has taken over</a> the city of Goma. The violence has displaced half a million people. Over 100 people have been killed, nearly 1,000 wounded, and 1,200 Congolese soldiers have surrendered. 
</p>
<p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          Protests erupted in <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-h3-8-kinshasa" target="_blank">Kinshasa</a>, targeting embassies of a handful of nations, particularly Rwanda, the US, France, Kenya, and Belgium. The UN and African Union have called for M23 to disarm, and international leaders are urging a ceasefire. The DRC accuses Rwanda of exploiting the region’s mineral wealth, while Rwanda denies involvement. 
</p>
<p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
         The DRC president, Félix Tshisekedi, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-h3-9-will-not-meet" target="_blank">will not meet</a> with Rwandan President Paul Kagame at the proposed peace summit. This attack has spiraled into a humanitarian crisis, with the UN warning of hundreds of thousands forced from their homes, severe food shortages, looted aid, overwhelmed hospitals, and the potential spread of disease.
</p>
        </mj-text>
