          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>🇬🇱 Greenlanders overwhelming don’t want to be part of the US</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">A new poll shows that <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-br2-12-85-greenlanders-opposed" target="_blank">85% of Greenlanders oppose</a> becoming part of the US, despite Donald Trump's renewed push to acquire the Arctic island. Trump claimed Greenland's residents "want to be with us" and has refused to rule out military action. Danish PM Mette Frederiksen, alongside European leaders, emphasized the need for Europe to unite against shifting US relations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">However, while many Greenlanders reject Trump, they are more interested in working toward their sovereignty. <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/gs-30-01-2025-br2-13-inuit-circumpolar-council" target="_blank">The Inuit Circumpolar Council</a>, representing all Inuit from Alaska, Canada, Chukotka, and Greenland, said the last few weeks had shown how important the Arctic is to the international agenda, but improving the status of Inuit lives is more important.</p>
        </mj-text>
