          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">How did the DRC become independent?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-30-3.png" alt="How did the DRC become independent?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), formerly known as the Belgian Congo, became independent on June 30, 1960, after a period of increasing pressure for decolonization and political change. The Congo was a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-f1-14-belgian-colony" target="_blank">Belgian colony</a> from 1908 after being privately owned by King Leopold II of Belgium from 1885 to 1908.</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">During <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-f1-15-the-colonial-period" target="_blank">the colonial period</a>, the Belgian authorities exploited the Congolese people, forcing them into harsh labor conditions, especially in rubber and mineral extraction. The 1950s brought rising decolonization movements and pressure on colonial powers weakened by the Second World War. The Congolese were no exception, and their independence movement gained momentum as nationalist leaders emerged, demanding an end to colonial rule.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">In 1959, Belgian officials announced plans to gradually transition to Congolese self-rule, which led to the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-01-2025-f1-16-round-table-conference" target="_blank">Round Table Conference</a> in Brussels from January to February 1960. Nationalist leaders advocated for immediate independence, while Belgian officials preferred a slower approach. Ultimately, an agreement was reached on June 30, 1960.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
